headline: Alexandria Real Estate Equities: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: PASADENA, Calif. (AP) — Alexandria Real Estate Equities Inc. (ARE) on Monday reported a key measure of profitability in its fourth quarter.  The real estate investment trust, based in Pasadena, California, said it had funds from operations of $411.8 million, or $2.39 per share, in the period.  The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.39 per share.
